ral world, and a generous spirit with an enviable work ethic.This is an examination of the writer through a new lens—one that more accurately captures Hemingway’s virtues as well as his flaws. Hutchisson situates Hemingway’s life and art in the defining contexts of the women he loved and lost, the places he held dear, and the specter of mental illness that haunted his family. This balanced portrait examines for the first time in full detail the legendary writer’s complex medical history and his struggle against clinical depression. The first major biography of Hemingway in over twenty years, this monumental achievement provides readers with a fresh, comprehensive look at one of the most acclaimed authors of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAuthors, AmericanxBiographyx20th centuryxBiographiesxBiographiesxBiography. 0aAuthors, AmericanxBiographyy20th centuryxBiographies. 0aAuthors, Americany20th centuryvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Adventurers & Explorers.2bisacsh  aErnist Hemingway.  aHitchisson.  abiography.  adepression.  alegend.  alove.  amental illness.  amyth.  a”balanced portrait”.  a”sensationalism”.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107452450 cprintz978027107534140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271079561?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271079561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271079561/original  a978-3-11-074524-5  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles